cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.SE

The paper discusses the use of machine learning models and their lack of transparency and auditability, which are common concerns in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the potential risks associated with using black-box models, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes a wrapper to improve the trustability of the resulting system, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
